text.__SUMMARY__:
Cyperus crispulus is a sedge of the family Cyperaceae that is native to  Western Australia.The perennial sedge typically grows to a height of 0.2 to 0.4 metres (0.7 to 1.3 ft) in height and has a tufted habit and produces brown flowers.
It is found in rock crevices amongst sandstone outcrops in the Kimberley region of Western Australia.
